arcus(PART 26): Batch 1 — critical fixes from the audit

Six P0/P1 fixes from docs/ARCUS-AUDIT-2026-05-28.md.

F5.1 — Date.now() id collisions in ChatInterface.tsx
Two messages created in the same millisecond would collide and React
keys would dedup, dropping one message. Added nextMessageId() that ORs
Date.now()*1000 with a monotonic counter — distinct ids even when
called twice in the same ms. Swept 7 message-id sites (5 user
messages + 2 agent messages + assistantMsgId). Suggestion-input ids
left as-is (those don't index any list).

FX.1 — User-ID casing inconsistency across lib/arcus
21 files used `userId.toLowerCase()` inline. A user whose email casing
varied between login and storage could split data across two
effective identities. Added lib/arcus/user-id.ts with
normalizeUserId() + isValidUserId() helpers. Swept all 21 lib/arcus
sites (autonomy, canvas-state, gmail-scope, memory, session-state,
agent-approvals, system-prompt, tools). API routes
(session.user.email.toLowerCase()) deferred — they're already
functionally equivalent.

F3.1 — Cron stale-lock could loop a slow agent forever
The pre-flight write set status='running' but NOT last_run_at. If
Vercel's 60s timeout killed the run before the post-completion
update, the row was left with a stale last_run_at. The 60-min
stale-lock check on the next tick would see that stale timestamp,
treat it as a crash recovery, and run the same agent again — could
loop indefinitely. Fix: write last_run_at = now at the SAME time as
status='running' so a timeout always leaves a fresh-ish timestamp.

F8.1 — Stage-2 idempotency: no dedup on agent create
A user double-clicking Confirm on the spec card could insert two
identical agent rows. Templates already had dedup; the LLM-driven
flow didn't. Added (user_id, name) dedup check at the top of
createScheduledAgent — returns the existing row when found instead
of inserting.

F1.1 — Stage-2 intercept lied on tool failure
The intercept ALWAYS emitted "**X** is live — first run …" even
when result.success === false (validation_error, integration_required,
agent_create_failed). User saw a confident success message but no
agent existed. Fix: branch on result.success. Failure path emits the
sanitized tool output instead of the fake live-message. Bonus:
catch-block now emits 'done' before close so the client doesn't fall
back to the legacy "stream finished unexpectedly" path.

F7.1 — saveMemory bypassed the user's opt-out toggle
The user can toggle memory off in settings. isMemoryEnabled was
checked in extractAndSaveInsights but NOT in the core saveMemory()
function. Manual memory_save tool calls + chat-route auto-extraction
+ every PART 23 path bypassed the toggle. Fix: saveMemory now checks
the toggle for 'ai' / 'agent_run' sources. Explicit 'user' sources
(manual add via UI, "remember X" extraction) still go through because
those are user-driven.

Type-check clean.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
